msgstr "Capire l'impatto"

#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "Why a single large JSON can hurt performance"
msgstr "Perché un singolo JSON di grandi dimensioni può danneggiare le prestazioni"

#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "Many i18n libraries store translations in a single JSON object provided via React context. When this object is large (thousands of keys), every component that consumes translations holds a reference to the entire dictionary. This means:"
msgstr "Molte librerie i18n memorizzano le traduzioni in un unico oggetto JSON fornito tramite il contesto React. Quando questo oggetto è grande (migliaia di chiavi), ogni componente che consuma le traduzioni mantiene un riferimento all'intero dizionario. Questo significa:"

#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "The JSON must be parsed on every page load — blocking the main thread."
msgstr "Il JSON deve essere analizzato a ogni caricamento della pagina, bloccando il thread principale."

#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "Context-based architectures can cause cascading re-renders when the locale changes, because every consumer is notified even if their specific keys didn't change."
msgstr "Le architetture basate sul contesto possono causare rendering a cascata quando la localizzazione cambia, perché ogni consumatore viene notificato anche se le sue chiavi specifiche non sono cambiate."

#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "During server-side rendering, the full dictionary is serialized into the HTML payload, increasing the document size that must be downloaded and hydrated."
msgstr "Durante il rendering lato server, l'intero dizionario viene serializzato nel payload HTML, aumentando la dimensione del documento che deve essere scaricato e idratato."

#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "The trade-offs of dynamic loading"
msgstr "I compromessi del caricamento dinamico"

#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "Splitting translations into per-route or per-namespace chunks can dramatically reduce the initial payload. But it introduces new challenges:"
msgstr "La scomposizione delle traduzioni in chunk per rotta o per namespace può ridurre drasticamente il payload iniziale. Ma introduce nuove sfide:"

#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "<0>Waterfall requests:</0> the app must first load, determine the locale, then fetch the right chunk — adding network round-trips."
msgstr "<0>Waterfall requests:</0> the app must first load, determine the locale, then fetch the right chunk — adding network round-trips."

#. 0: " "
#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "<0>Flash of untranslated content (FOUC):</0>{0} users may briefly see translation keys or a fallback language before the chunk arrives."
msgstr "<0>Flash of untranslated content (FOUC):</0>{0} users may briefly see translation keys or a fallback language before the chunk arrives."

#. 0: " "
#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "<0>Cache invalidation:</0>{0} updating translations requires cache-busting strategies to ensure users get fresh content without re-downloading unchanged chunks."
msgstr "<0>Cache invalidation:</0>{0} updating translations requires cache-busting strategies to ensure users get fresh content without re-downloading unchanged chunks."

#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "What this benchmark measures"
msgstr "Cosa misura questo benchmark"

#: src/components/pages/home/UnderstandingImpact.tsx
msgid "This test app provides a controlled environment — 10 pages with realistic content — to compare i18n libraries across three axes: the weight they add to your JavaScript bundle, the time spent parsing and rendering translated content, and the effectiveness of their code-splitting and lazy-loading strategies. Each library is integrated into the same app so results are directly comparable."
msgstr "Questa applicazione di test fornisce un ambiente controllato — 10 pagine con contenuti realistici — per confrontare le librerie i18n su tre assi: il peso che aggiungono al tuo bundle JavaScript, il tempo dedicato all'analisi e al rendering dei contenuti tradotti e l'efficacia delle loro strategie di code-splitting e lazy-loading. Ogni libreria è integrata nella stessa app in modo che i risultati siano direttamente confrontabili."

#: src/components/pages/home/WhyItMatters.tsx
msgid "Why These Metrics Matter"
msgstr "Perché queste metriche sono importanti"

#: src/components/pages/home/WhyItMatters.tsx
msgid "The bundle is the data shipped to every user across the globe. A larger bundle means longer download times — especially on slow 3G connections common in many regions. i18n libraries vary dramatically in their weight: from a few kilobytes to tens of kilobytes of runtime code, plus the translation files themselves."
msgstr "Il bundle rappresenta i dati inviati a ogni utente nel mondo. Un bundle più grande significa tempi di download più lunghi, specialmente sulle connessioni 3G lente comuni in molte regioni. Le librerie i18n variano drasticamente nel loro peso: da pochi kilobyte a decine di kilobyte di codice runtime, oltre ai file di traduzione stessi."

#: src/components/pages/home/WhyItMatters.tsx
msgid "Rendering & Hydration"
msgstr "Rendering e idratazione"

#: src/components/pages/home/WhyItMatters.tsx
msgid "Connecting a large JSON dictionary to every component creates a hidden dependency: any change in the translation context can trigger re-renders across the entire tree. During SSR hydration, parsing and attaching massive translation objects adds latency before the page becomes interactive — directly impacting Time to Interactive (TTI)."
msgstr "Il collegamento di un grande dizionario JSON a ogni componente crea una dipendenza nascosta: qualsiasi modifica nel contesto di traduzione può scatenare nuovi rendering in tutto l'albero. Durante l'idratazione SSR, l'analisi e l'aggiunta di enormi oggetti di traduzione aggiungono latenza prima che la pagina diventi interattiva, influenzando direttamente il Time to Interactive (TTI)."

#: src/components/pages/home/WhyItMatters.tsx
msgid "Dynamic Loading"
msgstr "Caricamento dinamico"

#: src/components/pages/home/WhyItMatters.tsx
msgid "Loading all translations upfront overloads the initial payload. Dynamic (lazy) loading splits translations by route or namespace, sending only what the current page needs. However, lazy loading introduces its own trade-offs: waterfall requests, flash of untranslated content, and caching complexity. Measuring both strategies is essential."
msgstr "Il caricamento di tutte le traduzioni in anticipo sovraccarica il payload iniziale. Il caricamento dinamico (lazy) divide le traduzioni per rotta o namespace, inviando solo ciò di cui la pagina corrente ha bisogno. Tuttavia, il lazy loading introduce i propri compromessi: richieste a cascata, flash di contenuti non tradotti e complessità della cache. Misurare entrambe le strategie è essenziale."

#: src/components/pages/about/AboutGrid.tsx
msgid "Why This Exists"
msgstr "Why This Exists"

#: src/components/pages/about/AboutGrid.tsx
msgid "Choosing an i18n library is an architectural decision with long-term consequences. Most comparisons focus on API ergonomics, but few measure the performance cost: how much weight does the library add to the bundle? How does it affect rendering when thousands of translation keys are loaded? Does lazy loading actually help or just shift the cost? This benchmark answers those questions with real data."
msgstr "Choosing an i18n library is an architectural decision with long-term consequences. Most comparisons focus on API ergonomics, but few measure the performance cost: how much weight does the library add to the bundle? How does it affect rendering when thousands of translation keys are loaded? Does lazy loading actually help or just shift the cost? This benchmark answers those questions with real data."

#: src/components/pages/about/AboutGrid.tsx
msgid "The same 10-page app is built once per library. We measure the production bundle (via rollup-plugin-visualizer), run Lighthouse audits for loading metrics, and use React Profiler to capture render times during locale switches. All tests run in CI on consistent hardware to ensure reproducible results."
msgstr "The same 10-page app is built once per library. We measure the production bundle (via rollup-plugin-visualizer), run Lighthouse audits for loading metrics, and use React Profiler to capture render times during locale switches. All tests run in CI on consistent hardware to ensure reproducible results."

#: src/components/pages/about/AboutHeader.tsx
msgid "AboutHeader"
msgstr "AboutHeader"

#: src/components/pages/about/AboutHeader.tsx
msgid "About This Benchmark"
msgstr "About This Benchmark"

#: src/components/pages/about/AboutHeader.tsx
msgid "This is an open-source test application — not a product or a company. Its sole purpose is to provide a realistic, multi-page React app where different i18n libraries can be integrated and measured under identical conditions."
msgstr "This is an open-source test application — not a product or a company. Its sole purpose is to provide a realistic, multi-page React app where different i18n libraries can be integrated and measured under identical conditions."

#: src/components/pages/about/WhatWeMeasure.tsx
msgid "Bundle size impact"
msgstr "Impatto sulla dimensione del bundle"

#: src/components/pages/about/WhatWeMeasure.tsx
msgid "The additional JavaScript bytes sent to users when the i18n library and its translation files are included. This directly affects download time on slow networks."
msgstr "The additional JavaScript bytes sent to users when the i18n library and its translation files are included. This directly affects download time on slow networks."

#: src/components/pages/about/WhatWeMeasure.tsx
msgid "Rendering overhead"
msgstr "Sovrapprezzo di rendering"

#: src/components/pages/about/WhatWeMeasure.tsx
msgid "How much extra time the library adds to React's render cycle. Libraries that inject translations via a single context provider can cause unnecessary re-renders across the component tree."
msgstr "How much extra time the library adds to React's render cycle. Libraries that inject translations via a single context provider can cause unnecessary re-renders across the component tree."

#: src/components/pages/about/WhatWeMeasure.tsx
msgid "Hydration cost"
msgstr "Costo di idratazione"

#: src/components/pages/about/WhatWeMeasure.tsx
msgid "During SSR, translation data is serialized into HTML. Large dictionaries increase the HTML payload and slow down hydration — the moment the page becomes interactive."
msgstr "During SSR, translation data is serialized into HTML. Large dictionaries increase the HTML payload and slow down hydration — the moment the page becomes interactive."

#: src/components/pages/about/WhatWeMeasure.tsx
msgid "Lazy loading effectiveness"
msgstr "Efficacia del caricamento lazy"

#: src/components/pages/about/WhatWeMeasure.tsx
msgid "Whether splitting translations by route or namespace actually reduces the initial load, and what trade-offs it introduces (waterfall requests, FOUC, cache complexity)."
msgstr "Se la scomposizione delle traduzioni per rotta o namespace riduca effettivamente il carico iniziale e quali compromessi introduca (richieste a cascata, FOUC, complessità della cache)."

#: src/components/pages/about/WhatWeMeasure.tsx
msgid "Locale switch speed"
msgstr "Velocità di cambio localizzazione"

#: src/components/pages/about/WhatWeMeasure.tsx
msgid "How fast the app can switch from one language to another at runtime — including fetching new translations, re-rendering components, and updating the DOM."
msgstr "Quanto velocemente l'app può passare da una lingua all'altra in esecuzione, includendo il recupero delle nuove traduzioni, il re-rendering dei componenti e l'aggiornamento del DOM."

